checkParameterizedTerm

public void checkParameterizedTerm(Term term)
                            throws SemanticWarning
Checks the provided parameterized term has the correct signature for its function enum.

This semantic check ensures the function signature matches what is provided by the function associated with the term t, a term with parameters.

checkRelationship

public void checkRelationship(Statement statement)
                       throws SemanticWarning
Checks the provided statement contains a relationship when necessary.

This semantic check ensures a statement provides a relationship when an object is present and does not provide a relationship when an object is absent. The attribute indicates the relationship between subject and object.

Specified by:

checkListUsage

public void checkListUsage(Statement statement,
                           Document document)
                    throws SemanticWarning
Checks the provided statement for improper use of LIST.

This semantic check ensures that a statement that has an object using the LIST function must have a relationship type of HAS_COMPONENTS or HAS_MEMBERS. All statements using LIST without having a proper relationship type will be pruned from the document and a semantic warning will be thrown.

Specified by:
checkListUsage in interface SemanticService
Parameters:
statement - Statement
Throws:
SemanticWarning - Thrown if the supplied statement fails the semantic verification check or an error occurs during semantic verification
See Also:
Statement

checkMultiNested

public void checkMultiNested(Statement stmt,
                             Document doc)
                      throws SemanticWarning
Checks that the provided statement is only nested at most one time. If the statement is nested more than once then it will be pruned from the document and a semantic warning will be thrown.

Specified by:
checkMultiNested in interface SemanticService
Parameters:
stmt - the statement to check for multi nesting
doc - the document containing the statement
Throws:
SemanticWarning - Thrown if the statement provided is nested more than once

checkAbundanceSubsets

public List<SemanticWarning> checkAbundanceSubsets(Term term)
Checks the provided abundance term term is semantically valid. If the provided term is not one of:
  • gene abundance
  • protein abundance
  • RNA abundance
this method returns immediately.

This check ensures valid function arguments are being used beyond the normal function and namespace value argument types. Refer to the BEL function specification for more information.

Specified by:
checkAbundanceSubsets in interface SemanticService
Parameters:
term - Term
